ya.org.il/english/  Ohr Chaya Center, Jerusalem]\n*[http://www.orothagalil.org/ Orot HaGalil College]\n*[http://www.schooly2.co.il/pelech_jer/page.asp?page_parent=63881 Pelech School Jerusalem]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090103065555/http://www.pninim.org/ Pninim Kiryat Moshe]\n*[http://shaanan.ac.il/ Shaanan Academic Religious Teachers' College]\n*[http://www.shareibina.com/  Sharei Bina Women's Center]\n*[http://www.shaalvim.org/sfw/  Shalvim Midrasha for Women]\n*[http://www.shearim.com/ Shearim College for Women]\n*[http://www.msy.org.il/ Shoshanat Yerushalaym]\n*[http://www.tiferetcenter.com/  Tiferet Center Beit Shemesh]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20081119064655/http://www.tomerdevorah.net/main.htm Tomer Devorah Seminary]\n*[http://www.yta.org.il/girls/ Torah Academy for Girls]\n*[http://toratreva.org/Joomla/index.php Torah Reva Yerushalaym]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Israeli Hebrew schools==\n*[http://acelearning.co.il/ Ace Academic Center]\n*[http://www.beitmargalit.com/en/ Beit Margalit Hebrew School]\n*[http://www.democratics.org.il/ Democratic School of Hadera]\n*[http://keren.torahindex.com/default.asp?iId=HILHG Keren HaYeled Hebrew School]\n*[http://www.nachalnovea.com/KiryatBreslev/GanYehudit/ganyehudit.htm Kindergarten Gan Yehudit]\n*[http://www.nachalnovea.com/ Nachal Novea Mekor Chochma]\n*[http://www.neveshmuel.org.il/ Neve Shmuel Boys High School]\n*[http://www.makorhatikvah.org/ Makor Ha Tikvah Hebrew School]\n*[http://boysschool.hartman.org.il/ Shalom Hartman Hebrew School]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070629021433/http://www.shevut-rachel.muni.il/aboutus.html Shvut Rachel Hebrew School]\n*[http://www.nachalnovea.com/KiryatBreslev/MagenAvot/magenavot.htm Talmud Torah Magen Avot]\n*[http://sites.torahindex.com/PinskKarlin/en/tat.htm Talmud Torah Pinsk Karlin]\n*[http://sites.torahindex.com/RavPealim/en/home.htm Talmud Torah Rav Pealim]\n*[http://sites.torahindex.com/ToratOlam/en/tat.htm Talmud Torah Torat Olam]\n*[http://sites.torahindex.com/Skvira/en/tat.html Talmud Torah Yakov Yosef]\n*[http://sites.torahindex.com/ZivHatorah/ Talmud Torah Ziv HaTorah]\n*[http://www.yta.org.il/ Torah Academy of Jerusalem]\n*[http://www.nachalnovea.com/KiryatBreslev/Yeshiva/yeshiva.htm Yeshiva Ketana Kiryat Breslev]\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Jewish communities by country]]\n*[[List of Israeli universities and colleges]]\n*[[List of synagogues in Israel]]\n*[[List of synagogues in the United States]]\n*[[List of Jewish communities in North America]]\n*[[List of Jewish communities in the United Kingdom]]\n*[[Structure and internal organization of the Israel Army]]\n\n{{Orthodox yeshivas in Israel}}\n\n[[Category:Israel religion-related lists]]\n[[Category:Judaism-related lists|Yeshivas]]\n[[Category:Lists of religious schools|Yeshivas, midrashas and Hebrew schools in Israel]]\n[[Category:Midrashim]]\n[[Category:Yeshivas| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{MOS|date=July 2013}}\nThis is a '''list of [[yeshiva]]s, [[midrasha]]s and [[Hebrew school]]s in [[Israel]]''' and the [[West Bank]].\n\nA [[yeshiva]] ([[Hebrew language|Hebrew]]: \u05d9\u05e9\u05d9\u05d1\u05d4) is a center in [[Orthodox Judaism]] where men can study the [[Torah]], the [[Talmud]], and develop their character. A yeshiva usually is led by a rabbi called a [[rosh yeshiva]] (head of the yeshiva). A midrasha ([[Hebrew language|Hebrew]]: \u05de\u05d3\u05e8\u05e9\u05d4) or seminary is an equivalent center for Jewish women.\n\n==Yeshivas==\n*HaYeshiva HaGehova Hebrew\n*Heichal HaTorah Tzion\n*[[Jerusalem College of Technology]]\n*Maale Efraim Hesder Yeshiva\n*Machon Benayah Yeshiva\n*Merkaz Herzog Center\n*Shaanan College for Education\n*Yeshiva Ateret Cohanim\n*Yeshiva Ayelet of Eilat\n*Yeshiva Bat Ayin\n*Yeshiva Toras Chaim\n*Yeshiva Mercaz Hatorah\n*Ohr Yerushalaim\n*Mesivta Adams D'Darnold\n*Yeshiva Chofetz Chaim\n*Yeshiva Beit Orot\n Yeshivat Beit Nochum M' Telz Stone\n*Yeshiva Bnei Akiva\n*Yeshiva Chemdat Yehuda\n*Yeshiva Darkhei Torah\n*Yeshiva Gedolah Ramat Sh