030M1|M1030M1 Motorcycle]]\n* [[Forklift truck]]\n* [[Oshkosh Striker]]\n* [[Rhino Runner]]\n* [[Mamba APC]]\n* [[Wiesel AWC|Wiesel 1]] \u2013 7\n* [[Ford F-Series]]\n* [[Chevy Tahoe]]\n\n==Unmanned combat vehicles==\n<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rsjpo.army.mil/images/UGS_Roadmap_Addendum_Jul12.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-05-15 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130215085332/http://www.rsjpo.army.mil/images/UGS_Roadmap_Addendum_Jul12.pdf |archive-date=2013-02-15 |df= }}</ref>\n* [[Dragon Runner]]\n* [[PackBot|iRobot 510 Packbot]]\n* [[XM1216 Small Unmanned Ground Vehicle]]\n* [[iRobot#FirstLook|iRobot 110 FirstLook]]<ref>[http://www.defensenews.com/article/20141115/DEFREG02/311150033/US-Army-Works-Toward-Single-Ground-Robot?odyssey=mod_sectionstories US Army Works Toward Single Ground Robot] - Defensenews.com, 15 November 2014</ref>\n* [[iRobot Warrior|iRobot 710 Warrior]]\n* [[Foster-Miller TALON]]\n* [[MARCbot]] IV\n* [[Remotec ANDROS]]\n* [[iRobot R-Gator]]\n* [[Squad Mission Support System]] (SMSS)\n* [[DOK-ING|M160]]\n\n==Experimental vehicles==\n* [[Joint Light Tactical Vehicle]] (JLTV)\n* [[Amphibious Combat Vehicle]] (ACV)\n* [[Armored Multi-Purpose Vehicle]] (AMPV)\n* [[Modular Advanced Armed Robotic System]] (MAARS)\n* [[Black Knight (Unmanned Combat Vehicle)]] \u2013 prototype only\n\n==See also==\n* [[Currently active military equipment by country]]\n* [[Vehicle registration plates of the United States Army in Germany]]\n* [[M-numbers]]\n* [[List of land vehicles of the U.S. Armed Forces]]\n* [[List of crew-served weapons of the U.S. Armed Forces]]\n* [[List of vehicles of the United States Marine Corps]]\n* [[List of weapons of the U.S. Marine Corps]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{US military utility vehicles}}\n{{US military navbox}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of currently active military vehicles|United States]]\n[[Category:Military vehicles of the United States|U.S. armed forces]]\n[[Category:United States mil